The paper deals with fine-grained complexity and reductions, which are topics typically studied in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The problems studied in the paper, such as Orthogonal Vectors, 3SUM, and Negative-Weight Triangle, are all related to data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves counting problems, which are often studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper deals with the Strong Exponential Time Hypothesis (SETH), which is a topic in computational game theory (cs.GT).
